Dear all,

way back in 1998 Colin McLarty raised the following question:

>Can the adjoint lifting theorem for triposes (from Andy Pitts's dissertation)
>be gracefully transported to regular categories (presumably
>with some supplemental conditions)? If so, the theory of
>realizability toposes could be radically simplified,
>among other things (see Japp van Oosten's dissertation).

has there been any progress on or toward this in the last 22 years?

Best regards,
David


